[Black "Chapter 5 Dragon Formation"]

{Black intends to enter Dragon territory with kingside fianchetto. Standard development won't suffice for the gambiteer. White should either pressure f7 with Qb3 to provoke ...e6; or in other lines play 7. e5 to discourage ...d6.}

1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 dxc3 4. Nxc3 Nc6 (4... g6 5. Nf3 Bg7 (5... Nc6 6. Bc4 d6 (6... Bg7 7. e5 (7. Qb3? Na5 8. Bxf7+ Kf8 9. Qd5 Nf6)) 7. Qb3 e6 8. Bf4 a6 (8... Na5 9. Bb5+ Bd7) 9. Be2) 6. Bc4 d6 7. Qb3 e6 8. Bf4) 5. Nf3 g6 {[%entry]} 6. Bc4 Bg7 7. e5 Nxe5 (7... Nh6 8. O-O O-O 9. Bf4) (7... Qa5 8. O-O Nxe5? 9. Nxe5 Bxe5 10. Nb5 Nf6 (10... a6 11. Qd5 (11. Bxf7+)) 11. Re1 Bb8 12. Rxe7+) 8. Nxe5 Bxe5 9. Bxf7+ Kxf7 10. Qd5+ Kg7 (10... e6? 11. Qxe5 Qf6 (11... Nf6 12. Nb5) 12. Qg3) 11. Qxe5+ Nf6 12. O-O d6 13. Qe2 *
